    "These sub-modules share an identical architecture, as both must predict numerical and categorical values.",
    "They differ only in the specific attributes they target and the temporal origin of their ground truth data.",
    "The input to the output module is the hidden representation 𝐻 from the Transformer block for a given time step.",
    "For numerical attributes, the module predicts a full probability distribution rather than a single point estimate, allowing it to capture the inherent uncertainty in its predictions.",
    "This is achieved by estimating the mean (𝜇) and standard deviation (𝜎) of the value in logarithmic scale."
